description: TO ADOPT A RESOLUTION THAT IT IS INEXPEDIENT AT THIS TIME, TO APPOINT A MINISTER FROM THE U.S. TO THE COURT OF RUSSIA.

TO AMEND THE BILL, (APP. 6/28/1809, 2 STAT L. 549), TO REMIT CERTAIN PENALTIES AND FORFEITURES, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES, BY ELIMINATING THE SECOND SECTION WHICH PRESERVES THE EXERCISE OF CERTAIN PROPERTY RIGHTS OF OWNERSHIP OF SLAVES OVER THE SAME AS IF TE ACT AFORESAID HAD NEVER BEEN PASSED, UNTIL THE LEGISLATURE OF THE SEVERAL STATES WITHIN WHICH ANY SUCH SLAVES MAY HAVE BEEN BROUGHT SHALL HAVE DISPOSED OF SAME ACCORDING TO THE PROVISIONS OF THE ACT.
